      'result': """The Remote Code Execution (RCE) vulnerability in PHPUnit's `eval-stdin.php` script is identified by **CVE-2017-9841**.

This vulnerability allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary PHP code through a malicious HTTP POST request. Specifically, the issue affects the `Util/PHP/eval-stdin.php` source file in PHPUnit. Attackers can exploit this by sending HTTP POST data beginning with a "<?php " substring to an exposed `/vendor/phpunit/phpunit/src/Util/PHP/eval-stdin.php` URI.

The vulnerability is present in PHPUnit versions prior to 4.8.28 and 5.x prior to 5.6.3. The core of the vulnerability lies in the `eval-stdin.php` script using `eval('?> ' . file_get_contents('php://input'))` to process raw POST data, allowing for code injection. The patch for this vulnerability replaced `php://input` with `php://stdin`, which is not populated in web contexts, thereby mitigating the RCE. This vulnerability has a CVSS 3.x base score of 9.8, categorizing it as critical."""
    }
  )
